{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|つま}}
From {{m|ja|端|tr=tsuma||side, edge}}, indicating the person who is ''at the side'' of someone: a [[spouse]].<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> Compare the {{etyl|en|-}} expression {{m|en|better half}}.

This term originally referred to either a male ({{m|en|husband}}) or female ({{m|en|wife}}) spouse. In modern usage, this term refers only to a female spouse.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

* {{s|one’s own wife}} {{ja-r|家%内|か%ない}}
* {{s|someone else's wife}} {{ja-r|奥さん|おくさん}}, {{ja-r|奥様|おくさま}}
* {{s|Kansai}} {{ja-r|嫁|よめ}}
* {{s|spouse in general}} {{ja-r|配偶者|はいぐうしゃ}}

{{ja-noun|つま}}

# a [[side dish]]
# a [[tangent]], a [[digression]], something to the [[side]] of the main thing

{{ja-noun|さい}}

# [[my]] [[wife]]
#* {{w2|ja|sc=Latn|石川啄木|Isikawa Takuboku}}, ''{{l|ja|sc=Latn||Romazi Nikki}}''
#*: {{quote|ja|sc=Latn|Yo wa '''Sai''' wo aisiteru; aisiteru kara koso kono Nikki wo yomase taku nai no da.|I love my '''Wife'''; it is precisely because I love her that I do not want her to read this Diary.}}
